> [{quoted}](name=Targons Blade,realm=NA,application-id=osqw6G4M,discussion-id=uo1BGuf5,comment-id=0000,timestamp=2017-01-26T00:34:47.453+0000)
>
> Does this also happen in Windowed mode or Borderless? If it does, then it&#x27;s likely your input file may be corrupt in some sort of way. I&#x27;d like you to complete a reset of the input file with the following steps.
> 
> You&#x27;ll want to log into the Client and leave it running in the background. Then complete the following:
> - Select &#x27;Open in Finder&#x27;
> - Right Click on &#x27;League of Legends&#x27;
> - Select &#x27;Show Package Contents&#x27;
> - Select &#x27;Contents&#x27;
> - Select &#x27;LoL&#x27;
> - Delete the folder named &#x27;Config&#x27; (Right Click, then select &#x27;Move to trash&#x27;, then empty your trash)
> 
> Once you&#x27;ve deleted the folder, hop into a custom match to confirm the change went through and test your smartpings out. You may also want to hop into your **Hotkeys** settings and ensure your bindings have been configured the way you want them. Let me know if this worked!

That ended up helping clearing out the problem.
